Class User

  • java.lang.Object
    • User

  • public final class User
extends java.lang.Object
    This class contains all user information and cascades into the other major data structures for this project. Contains a username, a hashed password, and a list of accounts associated with the user. Shoudl be contained in a list of Users in the main application
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Clark Chambers

      • addAccount

        public void addAccount(Account a)
                throws ElementPresentException
        Adds an Account to the accounts list for the User. Compares the hash code for the account to add with accounts already in list. Throws an exception if the hash code for the user is already found in the list.
        Parameters:
        a - The account to be added to the list.
        Throws:
        ElementPresentException - If account already exsits, throw this exception
        See Also:
        Account
